Terminalia and Genitalia. Male (
Figs. 27–28
). Ectoprocts oval; gonarcus wide vaulted; parameres close to each other terminal and far separated basal, pelta present; pulvini distinctive. Female (
Figs. 30–31
). Ventrovalvae triangular, with interdens; linguella distinctive; distivalvae nearly oval.
